+Implemented the C-011 React surface by updating `scripts/scaffold-tauri.sh` to emit a React 19/Vite 8/Tailwind 4 desktop/web scaffold with pinned PEM 3.0.0-alpha.0 and `@flint/react` git dependencies, local `@prometheus-ags/gen-ui-react` ContentBlock rendering, strict Component → Hook → Store layering, core-fed A2UI/Flint surface stores, shared-SQL PEM schema registration, Tauri-plugin entity transport/persistence on desktop, and PGlite local-first graph persistence on web; updated `scripts/scaffold-hybrid.sh` so publishable local packages exist before desktop dependency resolution. Also fixed pre-existing scaffold blockers (missing Vite HTML/node tsconfig, invalid `uuid` dependency, CommonJS `require`, incorrect `@sandpack/react` name) and added a `SKIP_INSTALL` verification seam. Shell syntax and generated-output boundary checks pass. Blocker/deviation: a clean pnpm consumer install cannot complete because the unpublished PEM git subpackage itself depends on `@prometheus-ags/entity-graph-core@workspace:*`; pnpm reports `ERR_PNPM_WORKSPACE_PKG_NOT_FOUND` outside the PEM monorepo. The dependency was not vendored or reimplemented because that would violate the adopt verdict and Rule 40; PEM must publish consumable packages (or replace workspace protocols in its packed artifact) before the generated app can typecheck end-to-end.
